text: Happy birthday to my friend, @SenatorCardin! Through years of public service, you've proven to be a dedicated and compassionate leader. I'm proud to work with you in Congress as we fight to make Maryland a better state for all.

Happy #WorldTeachersDay! As the son of a teacher, I watched my mom work day and night to help her students. Our teachers go above and beyond to help our kids believe in themselves and grow into successful leaders. Today, thank a teacher for the great work they do.

Proud to join @SenatorCardin, @ChrisVanHollen, & @RepRaskin in announcing that $530,000 is headed to MoCo for LGBTQ+ youth violence prevention programs. The LGBTQ+ community has faced endless attacks & we must work to ensure all Marylanders can feel safe. wusa9.com/article/news/commu…

Happy birthday, @RepUnderwood! Proud to partner with you on the Momnibus to address our nation's high maternal mortality rate. Your efforts to combat our health care disparities and give moms more support are inspiring. Thank you for all you do!
My full statement on the Motion to Vacate against Kevin McCarthy:

I'm proud to join @POTUS in recognizing October as National Youth Substance Use Prevention Month.

Over five million young adults have substance use disorder, and that number will continue to grow if we don't do more. Prevention is the first step to saving lives.

During #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek, we work to provide resources to those in need of mental health support. One in five adults experiences a mental health condition every year, and it's on us to help. To those struggling, know that I'm fighting for you in Congress and beyond.
My full statement on today's vote to avert a government shutdown:

Just now, the House passed a clean continuing resolution, without any extreme MAGA Republican policies, to help keep our government open.

This is a victory for the American people — and I was proud to vote for it.

Now, onto the Senate.

Today is the last day of National #RecoveryMonth, but it's not the last day of action. The @bmhsudtf will continue working to bring resources, treatment, and support to all fighting substance use and mental health disorders. We're never giving up.

More than 25% of adults living with serious mental health problems also have a co-occurring substance use disorder problem. These epidemics go hand-in-hand, and we must address both. This #RecoveryMonth, let's take steps to end these crises together.

Maryland will be among those hardest hit by a Republican shutdown. We had a deal in place, but House Republicans reneged. Now, Marylanders will pay the price. As members of @AppropsDems, @Call_Me_Dutch and I are fighting to keep the government's lights on.
baltimoresun.com/opinion/op-…
This is how the extreme MAGA Republicans govern:

124 years ago today, the #VFW was established, supporting veterans and their families throughout the country. Thank you to all of the @VFWHQ volunteers and to all of our veterans for their sacrifice and service.

Time is running out for House Republicans to stop the government shutdown.

Time is running out to protect federal workers, small businesses, children, and our rural communities.

And time is running out to put #PeopleOverPolitics.

The clock is ticking.

I commend @GovWesMoore, @MDStadiumAuth, and the @Orioles for their work in reaching this agreement, ensuring the team’s continued success, and driving economic opportunities in the city. As a lifelong fan, I join millions across our state in celebrating this news. Let's go O's!

After the Orioles clinched the AL East title last night, this news couldn't come at a better time! Not only for Orioles fans but also for the thousands of Marylanders who depend on the jobs this team brings to Baltimore. For Maryland, this deal is a win-win.

I join the nation in mourning Sen. Dianne Feinstein, whose life was defined by broken glass ceilings and fierce advocacy for human rights, especially for LGBTQ+ Americans. Much like her tenacity, her legacy in public service will never fade. Our thoughts are with her loved ones.

Over two million kids in the U.S. have a parent with substance use disorder. As a father of four, I know how hard it is to be a parent, but raising a child while fighting SUD is even more challenging. We must invest in prevention and treatment so parents can be parents.

Every September, we celebrate #RecoveryMonth to honor the 20 million in recovery from substance use and mental health disorders and shine a light on those we've lost. It's going to take all of us, working together, to combat this crisis, but we're up for the job.

Thank you, @macklemore and @MobilizeRecover, for your efforts to #endthestigma around mental health and substance use disorder. Many suffer in silence, but they shouldn't have to. Our loved ones need to know that help is available for all in need.

This #InternationalSafeAbortionDay, I join the @ProChoiceCaucus in raising awareness about destigmatizing abortion, protecting reproductive rights, and expanding access to abortion care.

Abortion is health care and we must work to ensure everyone has access.

House Republicans are threatening to shut down the government, forcing 144,165 federal workers in Maryland to work without pay.

And instead of looking for real solutions, they're demanding cruel cuts to education, child care, and more. Enough is enough. It's time to govern.

Substance use disorder doesn’t care if you're a Democrat or Republican, it affects us all. That's why efforts to combat the opioid epidemic need to be bipartisan too. This #RecoveryMonth, I invite all my Congressional colleagues to join me in the fight to save lives.

Three days before a government shutdown, extreme House Republicans continue to push for reckless funding cuts and culture war priorities that do NOTHING to prevent it. Folks, campaign season is over — it's time to govern.

What we need:
➡️To prevent a government shutdown

What we don't need:
➡️Troops forced to work without pay
➡️41.8 million Americans without SNAP benefits
➡️Failure to process small business loans

House Republicans need to get their act together.

Congratulations to my friend and fellow Marylander @SenatorCardin on officially being named Senate Foreign Relations Committee chair. With his incredible work in the U.S. Senate and on the issues brought before this committee, Senator Cardin’s appointment is well deserved.

Millions of Americans developed opioid use disorder and died because of Big Pharma's greed and disregard for human life. It's time the communities hit hardest by the opioid epidemic get the resources they need, and that money should come straight from Big Pharma's pocket.

Rates of relapse for those with a substance use disorder are similar to rates for other chronic illnesses like hypertension and asthma. Relapse isn’t a sign of failure, it just indicates a need for continued or modified treatment. Together, we can #EndTheStigma.
My statement on Senator Bob Menendez:

If the government shuts down this weekend, 2.1 million active-duty service members and reservists will go without pay. Shame on House Republicans for putting politics over our service members. It's simple: we must keep the government open.

Good news! Starting this week, #COVID19 test kits will be available to order by mail for FREE! Thank you, @POTUS, for ensuring folks have access to essential testing, and minimizing the spread of infection. Learn more here: covid.gov/tests

Last week, I got the chance to meet with @NEAToday to discuss how I can best support our educators in Congress. Our teachers work day and night to ensure our kids receive a good education. Investing in them and their success is just common sense.

While September is all about raising awareness for #RecoveryMonth, it’s also about taking action. That's why I introduced the IMPROVE Addiction Care Act to make it challenging for folks fighting substance use disorder to be prescribed opioids. It's just common sense.

While extreme Republicans are threatening to shut down the government, they are putting nutrition assistance at risk for nearly 7 million women and children who rely on WIC. On @AppropsDems, I am fighting to protect it no matter what. We can't let our children go hungry.
Wishing that all Marylanders observing #YomKippur have an easy fast today.

Maryland’s Good Samaritan Law protects anyone who helps with or is facing an overdose emergency. Calling 911 will not result in prosecution for possession of substances or affect parole status. 

This #RecoveryMonth, learn more here: beforeitstoolate.maryland.go…

One in five U.S. adults experiences mental illness each year, and all of these folks deserve treatment. This National #RecoveryMonth, remember that you are not alone. Call or text 988 for crisis counseling from the @988Lifeline.

Substance use disorder inflicts additional challenges on those in disadvantaged communities. It’s more difficult to get vital resources, causing an increased likelihood of a fatal overdose. That's why I’m working hard to ensure equitable access to treatment. #RecoveryMonth

I commend @GovWesMoore for declaring a state of emergency as folks across our state prepare for this storm.

For alerts, text MdReady to 211-631, or text MdListo for Spanish.

For more info, go to mdem.maryland.gov or follow @MDMEMA.

Maryland, stay vigilant and stay safe.

Good news! The @FCDFRS is receiving $9.7 million in SAFER grant funding to hire more firefighters in Frederick. Firefighters are often our first line of defense against natural disasters. With this new funding, Frederick will be better prepared to handle emergencies.

Proud to attend the groundbreaking for @BGCWC_MD's new clubhouse today with @SenatorCardin and @ChrisVanHollen. Last year, we delivered $4 million to help make this project a reality. Now, the Club will be able to serve even more kids in need and develop a teen center!

American Business Women's Day is an opportunity to celebrate the incredible contributions businesswomen have made throughout the country. Right now, 42% of business owners are women. Let's keep working to ensure there are more women-owned businesses across the nation!

Gun violence is an epidemic that takes the lives of over 40,000 Americans each year. I applaud the @WhiteHouse for creating an Office of Gun Violence Prevention, an essential step forward to save lives. Thank you, @POTUS. Let’s get to work.
Happy #NationalIceCreamConeDay to all the folks who enjoy ice cream cones as much as I do! Today, let's go support our local businesses and eat some delicious ice cream!

The opioid epidemic doesn't care if you're a Republican or Democrat: it impacts us all. Nearly 110,000 Americans died from overdoses last year. It's time to come together as a nation to end the opioid epidemic and save lives. Enough is enough.

Republicans claim to be the party of fiscal responsibility yet they are leading us toward another government shutdown.

In 2013, the government shutdown cost American taxpayers $2 billion. You don't need to be a businessman to know that's a giant waste of money.

No town, no neighborhood, no home has been left untouched by substance use disorder or mental illness. In Congress, I'm fighting to combat our nation's opioid epidemic for my nephew, Ian Trone. I won't ever give up. #RecoveryMonth

Last Congress, I helped pass the STANDUP Act to encourage states to implement evidence-based suicide prevention training in schools. Since then, @DrHollyWilcox and @LandonKrantz_MD created a guide for schools on how to select a program! Learn more here: piped.video/watch?v=V4cppIE1…

Thank you, @FASDUnited, for inviting me and @SenAmyKlobuchar to speak at your Red Shoes Gala! It's an honor to join you during #RecoveryMonth to advocate for more research and education on fetal alcohol spectrum disorders.

The Republican budget dramatically cuts funding for science and technology.

Good Lord.

10 days from a shutdown, Republicans continue to try to deliver on unrealistic and unsustainable campaign promises, which face an impossible path to passage.

It's time to start governing.

Today, the @bmhsudtf unveiled its 2023 legislative agenda, outlining the steps we're taking as a task force to address the opioid and mental health epidemics. With over 70 bills introduced this Congress alone, we are creating a path forward to end these intertwined crises.

On National Addiction Professionals Day, let’s celebrate our health care workers for their courageous efforts to save lives. In Congress, I'll continue to support these professionals by working to expand care and services to those most in need. #RecoveryMonth

The opioid epidemic started from the overprescribing of opioids in the 1990s. Now, we must set higher standards for prescribing these highly addictive drugs. Read more about what I'm doing in Congress to ensure there are more alternatives to pain relief.
baltimoresun.com/opinion/rea…

John Lewis called the right to vote precious, almost sacred. Today, I'm proud to join my fellow @HouseDemocrats in introducing the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to protect this right. We can't allow extremists to undermine our democracy and silence Americans.

It's heartwarming to see so many of my colleagues join the @bmhsudtf in #CongressGoesPurple to celebrate folks recovering from mental health & substance use disorders. Thank you to @RepAnnieKuster, @RepBrianFitz, and @RepLisaMcClain for your partnership. Recovery is for everyone.

Thank you, @MobilizeRecover, for being a leading partner in our effort to combat the opioid epidemic and for inviting me to speak at your conference today. It's because of folks like you that we're going to end the stigma surrounding substance use disorder and save lives.

The @bmhsudtf organizes #CongressGoesPurple to celebrate #RecoveryMonth every year. I’m proud to stand with my colleagues on both sides of the aisle to spread awareness and support those in recovery. No one should be alone in this fight.
Today we celebrate 76 years of the @usairforce serving and protecting our nation. To all our Air Force veterans and active duty service members, thank you for your service.

Mental health is health. Period. I commend @POTUS for taking action against health insurers that don't treat mental health the same as they do physical health care. Holding insurers accountable is key to ensuring more Americans can access this vital care.
politico.com/newsletters/pol…

I've gotten to know @RepWexton while serving on @AppropsDems and watched her fight to preserve Americans' fundamental rights day in and day out. I'm devastated to learn of this announcement and my thoughts are with her and her family during this time. We're here for you.

Today, we host #CongressGoesPurple for #RecoveryMonth to recognize the 20 million Americans in recovery and support those still struggling. Every community is impacted by these crises. Today, we unite behind a common cause: passing effective legislation to save lives.

Join Congress in wearing purple tomorrow for #CongressGoesPurple and share on social media — tag us and we’ll RT your post! We need to end the stigma surrounding substance use disorder and mental health in our country. Recovery is for everyone. #RecoveryMonth

September is #RecoveryMonth and although we use this month to celebrate those in recovery, we also remember those we've lost to overdoses. This month, I honor the memory of my nephew, Ian, who died from a fentanyl overdose in 2016. Everything I do in Congress is for him.

Today, we remember the four girls killed by white supremacists during the 16th Street Baptist Church bombing. This horrific attack reminds us that the fight for racial equality has come with immense loss and tragedy, and is still not over. We will never forget.

Thank you, @vitalstrat, for sending us a #SupportHarmReduction kit to display in our office. We've got to attack the opioid epidemic from every angle, and harm reduction is a crucial part of getting there. Let's save lives together.
L'Shanah Tovah to all celebrating #RoshHashanah! Wishing you a happy, healthy, and sweet New Year.

Today is the first day of National Hispanic Heritage Month, where we recognize and celebrate the rich history, culture, and contributions that the Latino community has made across the nation. I will always be committed to supporting this community in Maryland and beyond.

On National POW/MIA Recognition Day, let’s honor our brave service members who were prisoners of war or missing in action. We can never forget the noble, righteous sacrifice these soldiers made while serving their country, and we are eternally grateful.

Earlier this year, I introduced a bill with @RepEllzey and @RepPettersen to ensure naloxone is included in all airline medical kits. Just last month, a Southwest Airlines passenger experienced an overdose on a flight and needed naloxone. We must be prepared for anything.

It's great to see that @SheppardPratt is making a real impact on folks seeking mental health care. Last year, I was proud to deliver $1 million in #CommunityProjectFunding to expand their outpatient clinic. The more we invest in mental health treatment, the more lives we save.

On #NationalSoberDay, we celebrate those in recovery from substance use disorder and work to remove the stigma around getting help. If you or someone you know wants treatment click here: findtreatment.gov/

This #RecoveryMonth, remember to store prescribed opioids in a secure location and properly dispose of unused doses. Last Congress, my DUMP Opioids Act was signed into law for this very reason and helped to expand access to safe disposal boxes. Learn more: trone.house.gov/2021/07/29/t…

In 2018, Ethan Song was killed by an unsecured gun in a neighbor’s home. His story is tragic and sadly all too common. That's why I joined my @HouseGVP colleagues in signing a discharge petition to force a vote on Ethan’s Law, which would require secure firearm storage.

Thank you @NSCsafety, @ONDCP, @samhsagov, @RepPaulTonko, and my fellow co-chairs @RepAnnieKuster, @RepBrianFitz, and @RepLisaMcClain for all of the work you've done to fight the opioid epidemic and ensure naloxone is more accessible. Together, we will end this crisis.

Today, the @bmhsudtf hosted its second annual naloxone training with @GU_HOYA_Clinic, @DrGupta46, and @IncubatorGHAI! Naloxone is an easy-to-use, life-saving medicine that quickly reverses an opioid overdose. The more folks know how to use it, the more lives we can save.
Tune in LIVE to learn how to know the signs of a drug overdose and administer naloxone to save a life. #RecoveryMonth fb.watch/n1Cpwr9vZY/?mibexti…

The Child Tax Credit has been proven to combat childhood poverty. In 2021, Republicans terminated the expanded program, causing child poverty rates to double in 2022.

That's disgraceful.

We need to renew and expand the Child Tax Credit — it's really not that complicated.
Such a terrible tragedy. Our thoughts are with @Rep_Peltola and her loved ones during this time.

Today marks the 29th Anniversary of the Violence Against Women Act being signed into law, expanding resources to investigate violent crimes against women. I proudly voted to reauthorize this legislation last year and will always look out for Americans' safety and well-being.

Last year, 109,680 lives were lost due to a drug overdose. That’s 300 Americans every day and over 1 million over the next decade, and I won't stand for it. This #RecoveryMonth, we must take action to spread awareness about this growing crisis.

2023 is on track to be the deadliest year for mass shootings in recent American history, with almost 500 mass shootings this year alone. I'm proud to join my colleagues in urging @POTUS to do more to reduce gun violence because #EnoughIsEnough. Let's end this cycle of violence.

This #SuicidePreventionWeek, check in on your loved ones. Suicide is the second leading cause of death among people aged 10-14 and the third among those aged 15-24.

Help is available. Call, text, or chat the @988Lifeline for free 24/7 mental health support.

I proudly join the @ACLU and @ACLU_MD in urging @SecMayorkas to end the Frederick County Sheriff’s Office's federal immigration powers. Sheriff Jenkins' pattern of harassment under 287(g) is egregious, and it’s time we demanded equal treatment under the law for ALL Marylanders.

Every year, I host #CongressGoesPurple to celebrate the millions of Americans in recovery and to raise awareness about treatment. To those struggling with mental health or substance use disorder, know that we see you and stand with you.

Last year, nearly 110,000 Americans lost their lives to drug overdoses, the most ever in twelve months. It's heartbreaking, and we must do more to help folks fighting substance use disorder. This #RecoveryMonth, join me in working to end this epidemic once and for all.

On the 22nd anniversary of the 9/11 attacks, we remember those we lost, their loved ones, the survivors, and the first responders who saved lives that day. Here in Western Maryland, we honor these folks with a memorial in Hagerstown to ensure we #NeverForget that dark day.

If you or a loved one struggles with substance use disorder, it can be difficult to understand insurance coverage for treatment.

This #RecoveryMonth, learn more about your rights and coverage here: hhs.gov/opioids/treatment/in…

This #WorldSuicidePreventionDay, check in on your loved ones. Knowing the risk factors and warning signs can assist you in finding help for yourself or a loved one. The @988Lifeline is here to help at any time, day or night. Remember, it's okay to not be okay.

One in five fatal overdoses could be averted with naloxone. It’s simple, easy to use, and saves lives. It's a vital resource that everyone should know about. Learn more about this overdose reversal medication this #RecoveryMonth here: cdc.gov/stopoverdose/naloxon…

Vile anti-Semitism and Holocaust distortion from anyone—much less those in leadership—must be condemned.

As we seek peace and diplomacy in the Middle East, these comments will only stoke violence, hatred, and fear.

I join @StateSEAS in demanding an apology from President Abbas.

We have a mental health crisis in this country, and every day we don't invest in treatment puts lives at risk. This #RecoveryMonth, and every month, we need to fund programs, invest in resources, and make mental health care a national priority.

Substance use disorder should be treated as a public health issue, not a criminal one. For far too long, we've sent folks to prison instead of treatment facilities. Incarceration isn’t the solution, and it never was. #RecoveryMonth

Huge congratulations to Elham Tabassi on being recognized by @TIME as one of the most influential people in Artificial Intelligence. Elham works at @NIST in #MD06 and has done some outstanding work there. Thanks for making Maryland proud!

In the wake of so many mass shootings last year, I was proud to help pass the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act to reduce gun violence. The law increased background checks and expanded mental health care, but we must do more. Our kids deserve to feel safe at school. Period.

Team Trone's Regan stopped by Frederick County Goes Purple to raise awareness about the opioid epidemic. Nearly 110,000 lives were lost to overdoses last year, a true tragedy. That's why I'm committed to investing in prevention and treatment resources. Lives are on the line.

This #RecoveryMonth, we continue working to end the opioid epidemic and helping the over three million Americans fighting opioid use disorder find treatment.

If you or a loved one need help, dial 988 for free confidential counseling. You're not alone in this fight.

Team Trone’s Annaston had a wonderful time at Washington Goes Purple last week to celebrate #RecoveryMonth! Inspired by this movement and @Emily_N_Keller, I'm proud to have brought Congress Goes Purple to DC to encourage further investment in treatment and recovery resources.

The mental health crisis is only getting worse, and this shortage of health care professionals could have devastating consequences for our students.

I'm fighting every day in Congress to bring more mental health funding to these schools and give our kids a helping hand.

I proudly voted for the #AmericanRescuePlan to ensure Marylanders can access reliable broadband. In this day and age, internet access is essential to receiving a good education. With this new funding, we're leveling the playing field and setting our future leaders up for success.

During September, join me in celebrating #RecoveryMonth to recognize the over 20 million Americans recovering from substance use disorder. We need to #EndTheStigma surrounding mental health and substance use disorder in our country. Recovery is for everyone.

Happy birthday to my very good friend and fellow @bmhsudtf co-chair, @RepAnnieKuster! We couldn't make strides to end our mental health and opioid epidemics without your partnership. Thank you for always sticking by my side as we fight this crisis together.

Extreme Republicans are once again pushing for a border wall, a 6th century solution that only villainizes immigrants and neglects to provide real solutions to the fentanyl crisis. As a member of @AppropsDems, I will proudly vote against this ridiculous spending bill.

Last week, I stopped by @DetrickUSAG to celebrate the grand opening of Building 808! Fort Detrick is home to some of the top biomedical researchers in the country. With this expansion, we are well on our way to ensuring America is ahead in the fight against foreign adversaries.

Happy Labor Day to America's workers! In Congress, I will always fight to protect our workers and continue to create good-paying jobs that future generations can count on. By investing in our workforce, we're building a better tomorrow for all.

Today marks the start of Recovery Month, when we celebrate the over 20 million Americans in recovery from mental illness and substance use disorder. This month and every month, we fight for these folks and those still battling these diseases. Together, we can and will save lives.

On International Overdose Awareness Day, we remember those lost to addiction and the over one million empty chairs left at family dinner tables, including my own.

But today, we also reaffirm our commitment to fighting for those in the shadows of this disease. Let's get to work.

I was honored to attend the ribbon cutting of the new Crisis Center in Frederick. In 2022, Maryland lost over 2,500 of its own to drug overdoses and 500 to suicide. Enough is enough, so I delivered $1.5 million in Community Project Funding to this center. It's time to save lives.

And while this funding is still making its way to state and local governments, the American Rescue Plan continues to fund broadband expansion, which I just announced! It's about time that every Marylander can access health care, education, and jobs. trone.house.gov/2023/08/28/c…

That's a great question. And, you're right, it's ridiculous that affordable, high-speed interest hasn't reached many rural areas in our state. So, last Congress, I voted for the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act to deliver over $100 million to Maryland to expand broadband.

Folks, this is great news!

For too long, Americans have paid far too much for lifesaving prescription drugs. Today, thanks to the Inflation Reduction Act, that's changing.

Health care is a right — plain and simple — and we're fighting to ensure it's accessible to ALL Americans.

Studies show that over 25% of fatal overdoses could be averted if more Americans carried naloxone. Tune in to learn how you could save a life. Thank you @SecBecerra, @HHSGov, @DrGupta46, and @ONDCP for hosting!

America is facing a mental health epidemic, so I voted for the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act to deliver much-needed resources to the frontlines of this crisis and save lives. This funding will go a long way to provide help to those who need it most.
hhs.gov/about/news/2023/08/2…

I'm excited to announce that over $43 million in the latest Emergency Connectivity Funding is coming to schools and libraries across Maryland’s Sixth District. As the proud son of a teacher, I will always fight for high-quality education for all students.
trone.house.gov/2023/08/28/c…

The March on Washington was a powerful display of how we can unite as members of this democracy and fight for what we believe in. 

In Congress, I will always fight against inequalities that exist even today, promising a brighter future for the next generation.

On #WomensEqualityDay, we recommit ourselves to building a better, more inclusive nation for all. Today, women make 84 cents for every $1 men make, and that's far from equal. It's on all of us to work toward gender equality, and in Congress, I'll do just that.

I proudly join @ProChoiceCaucus for #ReproductiveFreedom Day of Action. Since #RoevWade was overturned, abortion access has been banned for millions of Americans. Abortion is health care, and folks must have the freedom to make their own health care decisions. Plain and simple.

2021 was the second year in a row in which guns were the leading cause of death among American children, surpassing cars, drug overdoses, and cancer. It's outrageous that we still haven't done more to keep our children safe. We need gun reform, and we need it now.
I supported the #InflationReductionAct because I believe everyone should have access to lifesaving medication like insulin. We’ve taken on Big Pharma before, and we will do it again.

Our country is experiencing a workforce shortage, and returning citizens are ready to work. Unfortunately, too many employers are hesitant to hire folks with a criminal record. My Fresh Start Act would streamline the record expungement process, giving folks a #SecondChance.

Out of 3,606 Medicaid-enrolled adolescents fighting addiction, only 68 received Medication-Assisted Treatment. That’s a disturbingly low number for such a life-saving treatment. I introduced the IMPROVE Addiction Care Act to connect more opioid overdose survivors to treatment.

Great piece by Blythe Maynard on recognizing the signs of substance use disorder and letting our loved ones know that it's OK to ask for help. With Maryland's fatal overdose rate nearly 85% higher than the national average, it's on all of us to end this epidemic.

The sentencing disparity between crack cocaine and powder cocaine is one of the clearest examples of systemic racism in our judicial system. That’s why I’m determined to pass the #EQUALAct to eliminate the 18:1 disparity and make progress on creating a fair judicial system.

Last Congress, I proudly supported the #InflationReductionAct. Since being signed into law, we've opened 80 major clean energy manufacturing facilities, equal to the previous 7 years combined. This law is a meaningful step in our fight against climate change.

I introduced the Public Safety Officer Support Act so families like the Smith family can get support. First responders experience more trauma in a year than many of us experience in a lifetime. It's about time we treated mental & physical injuries the same for our brave officers.

Thank you @Emily_N_Keller and @BeforeIts2Late, for providing Team Trone with Naloxone training at MACo last week. Naloxone is a medicine that rapidly reverses an opioid overdose, and the more folks know how to use it, the more lives will be saved.

Allowing pretrial detainees to receive Medicaid coverage is a no-brainer, yet the Medicaid Inmate Exclusion policy strips away the right to due process. My Due Process Continuity of Care Act would restore these rights because, in this country, you’re innocent until proven guilty.

103 years ago, the #19thAmendment was ratified, granting women the right to vote. Let this serve as a reminder that democracy works best when everyone has a seat at the table. And rest assured, I will always fight for gender equality and civil liberties.

Did you know: Medicare prescribers are not notified of their patients' nonfatal overdose history when prescribing opioids? My IMPROVE Addiction Care Act would fix this oversight and ensure prescribers have all the necessary information they need to keep patients safe.

Another reminder of how the opioid epidemic impacts us all. Overdoses can happen anywhere at any time, and we must be prepared. I introduced a bill to require naloxone on airplanes for this very reason, and if signed into law, lives will be saved.
abcactionnews.com/news/local…

Incarcerated individuals are 129 times more likely to die of a drug overdose in the first 2 weeks after release. We must ensure they can get support while still in prison, that's why I introduced the Reentry Act to restart Medicaid benefits and get these folks the help they need.

Attention Native American and Tribal Service members! The @DeptVetAffairs is hosting a Tribal Veteran Symposium to discuss benefits and services you may qualify for, including the #PACTAct, today from 3-6pm. Check it out! va.gov/outreach-and-events/e…

One year ago, the #InflationReductionAct was signed into law, lowering health care costs, capping prescription drug costs, and creating clean energy jobs. With this historic law, we are growing the middle class, all while ensuring corporations finally pay their fair share.

We've got to break down the stigma surrounding naloxone and make it an essential part of all medical kits. Period. These restaurant workers know all too well that an overdose can happen anywhere, and we all must be prepared. Lives are on the line.
nytimes.com/2023/08/15/dinin…

Over 70 million Americans have criminal records that appear in routine background checks, preventing them from accessing jobs, housing, and health care. My Fresh Start Act would streamline record expungement for those eligible and give these folks a real chance at a better life.

Moms deserve recognition for their dedication both at home and in the workforce. We must pass the Equal Rights Amendment to ensure every working mom gets the pay they rightfully deserve. #ERANow #MomsEqualPayDay

Happy birthday, @RepMaxineWaters! Proud to partner with you on criminal justice reform in Congress, including our Workforce Justice Act to ban the box on job applications nationwide. I know that together, we can get it done!

It's been 78 years since #VJDay and the end of World War II. On this momentous day, we celebrate by honoring our veterans and thanking them for their service. As the son of a WWII veteran, you have my word that I will always fight for our #veterans in Congress.

Internet is not a luxury, it’s a necessity, yet too many Marylanders lack access to reliable broadband. That's why I was proud to help pass the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act to invest $267 million into Maryland’s broadband deployment.
